  "raw_text": "Offer receipt\n\nThe method and location of bid receipt must be specified in the solicitation of offers.\n\nHere are the acceptable methods for offer submission and their conditions:\n\nIn writing and submitted to the specified receiving unit: applicable for all ($) dollar values\n\nIn writing and submitted directly to the buyer: for offers below $25,000 for goods and $40,000 for construction and services, including all applicable taxes\n\nVerbal submission by telephone:\n\nfor offers below $25,000 for goods and $40,000 for construction and services, including all applicable taxes\n\nfor any ($) dollar value in cases of documented extreme urgency, the director's approval is mandatory\n\nOn electronic media (e.g., DVD s, USB keys, CD s) and submitted to the specified receiving unit\n\nBy facsimile\n\nCanada Post Corporation’s Connect service\n\nIn situations where a particular method of response is deemed not acceptable, you must clearly indicate this in the solicitation document and in the Notice of Proposed Procurement (NPP).",
  "markdown_text": "Offer receipt\n\nThe method and location of bid receipt must be specified in the solicitation of offers.\n\nHere are the acceptable methods for offer submission and their conditions:\n\nIn writing and submitted to the specified receiving unit: applicable for all ($) dollar values\n\nIn writing and submitted directly to the buyer: for offers below $25,000 for goods and $40,000 for construction and services, including all applicable taxes\n\nVerbal submission by telephone:\n\nfor offers below $25,000 for goods and $40,000 for construction and services, including all applicable taxes\n\nfor any ($) dollar value in cases of documented extreme urgency, the director's approval is mandatory\n\nOn electronic media (e.g., DVD s, USB keys, CD s) and submitted to the specified receiving unit\n\nBy facsimile\n\nCanada Post Corporation’s Connect service\n\nIn situations where a particular method of response is deemed not acceptable, you must clearly indicate this in the solicitation document and in the Notice of Proposed Procurement (NPP).",
  "provenance_paths": {}
